<head>
<title> Thousands Virtually Join Aspen Summit  -- PFF</title>
</head>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/pff/notebook.gif" LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000"> <ul><blockquote><a href="/pff"><img src="/pff/pffdoc.gif" align="right" border="0"></a>
<p>
<font size="-1">
For Immediate Release<br>
August 21, 1995 <br>
Contact: Rick O'Donnell <br>
202/484-2312
</font>
<p>
<center>
<h2> Thousands Virtually Join Aspen Summit </h2>
</center> 
<p>

The leaders of Cyberspace gathered for the Aspen Summit '95 broke new ground today by simultaneously carrying on conversations face-to-face and on-line. The discussion among two hundred leading Cyberspace thinkers meeting at the Ritz-Carlton in Aspen, Colo., was carried to thousands on the Internet. 
<p>

"What we're doing in Aspen is trying to turn all the hype and cyberbabble into cybersense. While we brought leading  thinkers together in Aspen to work an a clear vision, we also involved the Cyberspace community itself,"  said <a href="/pff/people/director.html#Eisenach">Jeffrey A. Eisenach</a>, president of The Progress & Freedom Foundation which is hosting Aspen Summit '95.
<p>
On-line moderators posted real-time bulletins about the discussion in Aspen on the Aspen Summit '95 Homepage, while those logged onto the page posted comments that were shared with the participants back in Aspen. The Homepage received 6,032 hits during the days proceedings.
<p>
Monday was the first day of the two day Summit, and the Homepage will be in use again Tuesday 11:00 am to 7:00 pm EST.  To access the Homepage type: <a href="http://aspen.pff.org">http://aspen.pff.org</a>
<p>
"What we saw today in Aspen and on the Homepage was that the issues of how information technology is going  to change America are not confined to either the political right or left. People from diverse backgrounds are coming together to define a vision for what America can achieve in the Knowledge Age," said <b>Jay Keyworth, </b> chairman of the Foundation.

Tomorrow the Summit will continue with sessions on the Marketplace and Role of Government.  Among the 26 lead discussants will be: <b>Senate Minority Leader Tom Daschle </b>  (D-SD), <b> <a href="http://www.house.gov/ehlers/welcome.html">Congressman Vernon Ehlers </a></b>(R-MI), <b> Alvin Toffler</b>, author of <i>Creating a New Civilization</i>, and <b>John Gage </b>of  Sun Microsystems.

The Progress and Freedom Foundation is a non partisan research and educational organization dedicated to creating a  positive vision  of the future founded in the historic principles of the American idea.
<p>
<center>
<a href="/pff/><img alt="PFF Home Page" border=0 width=234 height=32 src="multi/gif/pff-footer-home.gif"></a>
</center>
</blockquote></ul><p><br><center><a href="/pff/footer.map"><img src="/pff/footer.gif" border="0" ISMAP></a></center></BODY>
